Retweets vs favorites

Expectedly there seems to be strong positive correlation between favorites(likes) and retweets, we will be using retweets as success metric from now on.

Tweet lengths

Boxplot shows that especially @NordVPN and @FreedomeVPN focus mostly on long tweets, while @expressvpn has high variation in tweet lengths. Box shows the 2nd quartile to 3rd quartile (50% center) of tweets, while horizontal line is the median value.

However, there doesn’t seem to be correlation between tweet length and retweet count:

cor(tweets_all$retweetCount, tweets_all$tweet_length)
## [1] 0.03206332
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

When do VPNs tweet?

Apart from @expressvpn the inspected accounts seem to post mostly during work hours. @NordVPN interestingly has three peaks; 4am, 9am and ~3pm-7pm (maybe trying to reach audience across different time zones).

@NordVPN tweets on very steady pace over the week, while others tweet less during weekends.

Tweeting during weekend has slightly worse performance retweet -wise during weekends as well. This might be skewed because of only one company tweeting though.

Tweets trended over time

@NordVPN has had impressive pace since the creation of their Twitter handle, although retweet amounts are low.
